$ HTMLElement: inert
@ inert

If an → development/web/HTML/DOM/API/interfaces-classes/HTMLElement[HTMLElement's] `inert` attribute is set to `true`, the → development/web/browser[browser] ignores user input for that element.

In the following example, the text *This text becomes inert* is not selectable:
gh|about-HTML-DOM-API|/HTMLElement/inert.html||

sa:

  The → development/web/HTML/attributes#html-global-attributes[global HTML attribute] `inert`.

  `→ development/web/HTML/DOM/API/interfaces-classes/HTMLElement`
